Official Press Release | Ministry of Youth Affairs & Sports 
A Historic Moment for ABC Fitness Firm 🇮🇳

We are deeply honoured and proud to have ABC Pro Basketball League Season 4 officially inaugurated by Union MoS Smt. Raksha Khadse under the esteemed banner of the Ministry of Youth Affairs & Sports.

This moment reflects not only our dream but the collective aspiration of thousands of young athletes across Maharashtra. With over 5,000+ participants, 310 elite players and 19 teams, this season stands as a tribute to the vision of Hon. Prime Minister Narendra Modi for a Viksit Bharat and the goals of Khelo Bharat Niti 2025.

We thank the Ministry, our partners, and every coach, parent, and player for believing in our mission.
We remain committed to building India’s biggest and most impactful junior basketball platform where every child finds the stage they deserve.

This is just the beginning. The future of Indian basketball is here. And it starts young. 🏀🔥

KHANDESH HEATS FINISH STRONG! 🔥
Khandesh Heats ended their campaign on a high in Day 5 Game 4, securing a commanding 40-16 win over Krisala PCMC Stallions in the Under 17 Girls clash! 🏀💪

Though both teams won’t be advancing further in the league, the Heats showed incredible heart, hustle and teamwork till the very end. 💯
They may not be in the next round, but they left the court with pride and purpose!

CHITALE WARRIORS STUN WITH A FIGHTBACK! 🔥
Pune Chitale Warriors pulled off a brilliant turnaround in Day 5 Game 2, coming back from a 15-point deficit to defeat the Kolhapur Jaguars 55-53 in a nail-biting finish! 

In the post-match moment, the coach shared how proud he was of the team’s never-give-up attitude and mental toughness — a big win for their confidence moving forward! 🙌

Player of the Match: @imraann._.07 
With 22 points, he not only led the comeback but also became the highest scorer of the tournament so far! 🔥👏
